SIMPLE: limb
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Limb
<hw>Limb</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>lim</ets>, AS. <ets>lim</ets>; akin to Icel. <ets>limr</ets> limb,
<ets>lim</ets> branch of a tree, Sw. & Dan. <ets>lem</ets> limb; cf.
also AS. <ets>li⟦edh⟧</ets>, OHG. <ets>lid</ets>, <ets>gilid</ets>, G.
<ets>glied</ets>, Goth. <ets>li⟦thorn⟧us</ets>. Cf. <er>Lith</er>,
<er>Limber</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A part of a tree which extends
from the trunk and separates into branches and twigs; a large
branch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An arm or a leg of a human being; a leg, arm, or
wing of an animal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A second Hector for his grim aspect,⟦br⟧
And large proportion of his strong-knit <qex>limbs</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A thing or person regarded as a part or member of,
or attachment to, something else.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That little <qex>limb</qex> of the devil has cheated the
gallows.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An elementary piece of the mechanism of a
lock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Limb of the law</b></col>, <cd>a lawyer or an officer of
the law.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <au>Landor.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Limb</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Limb
<hw>Limb</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To supply with
limbs.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To dismember; to tear off the limbs of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Limb</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Limb
<hw>Limb</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>limbus</ets> border. Cf.
<er>Limbo</er>, <er>Limbus</er>.]</ety> <def>A border or edge, in
certain special uses.</def> <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
border or upper spreading part of a monopetalous corolla, or of a petal,
or sepal; blade.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The border
or edge of the disk of a heavenly body, especially of the sun and
moon.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The graduated margin of an arc or circle,
in an instrument for measuring angles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Limbat</ent>⟦br⟧
